README.md:92:The smoke runner builds all workspaces, probes or starts the API and Web dev servers, invokes the CLI through the workspace-linked built entrypoint, performs login → session → project selection → registry → management → chat checks, and cleans up child processes and the temporary CLI config directory on success, failure, or timeout. Its logs are prefixed with `[smoke]` stage markers plus child process exit codes so startup, reachability, CLI, provider fallback, and cleanup failures are easy to localize without printing auth material.
